item.title: CVE-2020-7836|2024-09-17T03:28:29.004Z -- voiceye -- wsactivebridgees
item.description: VOICEYE WSActiveBridgeES versions prior to 2.1.0.3 contains a stack-based buffer overflow vulnerability caused by improper bound checking parameter given by attack. It finally leads to a stack-based buffer overflow via access to crafted web page.
